A project to provide YUI3 modules for dojox.gfx mostly running on top of
the YUI internals.

BEWARE this is just a sketch for now...

Notes
-----

* The dojo.requireIf doesn't work well.
* It renders some SVG in Google Chrome as is if the required renderer 
files are included as script tags.


Build
=====

# copy the dojo/dojox sources to the vender folder
cp -r dojo dojox vendor/
# build it
jake
# get the ready-to-use YUI3 module files
cp -r src/dojox-gfx your-3rd-party-yui3-modules-folder


Current Usage
=============

Y.use('gallery-dojox.gfx',
      // for now also:
      'gallery-dojox.gfx.svg', 'gallery-dojox.gfx.svg_attach',
function(Y) {
    var dojo = Y.dojo, dojox = Y.dojox;

    var surface = dojox.gfx.createSurface('nodeId', 300, 300);
    //
    // surface.createRect(...)
    //
});


